Guinea â€™s government and China
International Water & Electric Corp. signed an agreement for the
construction of a $526 million hydroelectric dam.  The West African nation will contribute 25 percent of the
funding for the project, about 150 kilometers (90 miles)
northeast of the capital, Conakry, and China International Water
& Electric the rest, according to the agreement.  The Keleta dam will have capacity of 240.5 megawatts,
Energy Minister Papa Koly Kourouma said during a signing
ceremony. Construction will begin by December and last 48
months, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
